<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Boltons raises half yr shr, div slips.</title>
<headline>Boltons raises half yr shr, div slips.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1996-10-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended Aug 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     65.0	  vs 60.6</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 10.5	  vs 12.0</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   2.85	  vs 3.14</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   8.99	  vs 9.63</p>
<p>    Tax			 2.81	  vs 3.08</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   3.35	  vs 2.59</p>
<p>    Turnover		  242.56	vs 238.44</p>
<p>Full name: Bolton Industrial Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company holds a 74.1 percent stake in Bolton Footwear Ltd and a 34.6 percent stake in Cargo Carriers Ltd.</p>
<p>In a separate announement, directors said a preference dividend of 5.5 cents per share for the six months ending December 31, 1996 had been declared payable to holders of 5.5 percent cumulative preference shares registered on December 6. Payment will be made around December 27.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
